{"application": "software-mentions", "version": "0.8.0", "date": "2024-10-07T11:56+0000", "md5": "FCF509185A8807982D9373DFDC46874E", "mentions": [{"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Clique", "normalizedForm": "Clique", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 6}, "context": "Clique Averaging.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00332486629486084}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00024372339248657227}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 7.152557373046875e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Clique", "normalizedForm": "Clique", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 6}, "context": "Clique Averaging allows us to reduce the bias in the momentum by using the clique-level average gradient g", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 8.45193862915039e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 7.736682891845703e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Clique", "normalizedForm": "Clique", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 6}, "context": "Clique Averaging can in turn be used to implement an effective momentum.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 9.40561294555664e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00494539737701416}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Clique", "normalizedForm": "Clique", "offsetStart": 5, "offsetEnd": 11}, "context": "With Clique Averaging, removing a single edge has a small but noticeable effect.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00018554925918579102}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 3.1828880310058594e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Clique", "normalizedForm": "Clique", "offsetStart": 7, "offsetEnd": 13}, "context": "Adding Clique Averaging requires gradients to be sent separately from the model parameters: the number of messages exchanged between nodes is therefore twice their number of edges.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00031375885009765625}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.9073486328125e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Clique", "normalizedForm": "Clique", "offsetStart": 8, "offsetEnd": 14}, "context": "Without Clique Averaging, removing edges has a small effect on convergence speed and variance, but the convergence speed is too slow to be practical.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00043898820877075195}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.7894973754882812e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Clique", "normalizedForm": "Clique", "offsetStart": 11, "offsetEnd": 17}, "context": "When using Clique Averaging, removing up to 5 edges does not noticeably affect the convergence speed and variance.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.013491988182067871}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 4.172325134277344e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Clique", "normalizedForm": "Clique", "offsetStart": 12, "offsetEnd": 18}, "context": "Recall that Clique Averaging induces a small additional cost, as gradients and models need to be sent in two separate rounds of messages.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 6.92605972290039e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.4066696166992188e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Clique", "normalizedForm": "Clique", "offsetStart": 12, "offsetEnd": 18}, "context": "We proposed Clique Averaging to remove the bias in gradient computation due to non-homogeneous averaging neighborhood by averaging gradients only with other nodes within the clique.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002956986427307129}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Clique", "normalizedForm": "Clique", "offsetStart": 16, "offsetEnd": 22}, "context": "(4) We show how Clique Averaging can be used to implement unbiased momentum that would otherwise be detrimental in the heterogeneous setting; (5) We demonstrate through an extensive experimental study that our approach removes the effect of label distribution skew when training a linear model and a deep convolutional network on the MNIST and CIFAR10 datasets respectively; (6) Finally, we demonstrate the scalability of our approach by considering up to 1000-node networks, in contrast to most previous work on fully decentralized learning which performs empirical evaluations on networks with at most a few tens of nodes (Tang et al., 2018;Neglia et al., 2020;Lin et al., 2021;Esfandiari et al., 2021;Kong et al., 2021).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.09219247102737427}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0030930638313293457}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Clique", "normalizedForm": "Clique", "offsetStart": 20, "offsetEnd": 26}, "context": "Figure 6 shows that Clique Averaging (Algorithm 3) reduces the variance of models across nodes and slightly accelerates the convergence on MNIST.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.030932605266571045}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 5.9604644775390625e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Clique", "normalizedForm": "Clique", "offsetStart": 27, "offsetEnd": 33}, "context": "Implementing momentum with Clique Averaging.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0010820627212524414}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0005635619163513184}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Clique", "normalizedForm": "Clique", "offsetStart": 33, "offsetEnd": 39}, "context": "Figure 8 shows that even without Clique Averaging, D-Cliques converge faster and with lower variance.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.001529395580291748}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.0742416381835938e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Clique", "normalizedForm": "Clique", "offsetStart": 34, "offsetEnd": 40}, "context": "We address this problem by adding Clique Averaging to D-SGD (Algorithm 3), which essentially decouples gradient averaging from model averaging.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0010792016983032227}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00026530027389526367}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Clique", "normalizedForm": "Clique", "offsetStart": 37, "offsetEnd": 43}, "context": "We show the results with and without Clique Averaging with momentum in both cases, as momentum is critical for obtaining the best convergence speed on CI-FAR10.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 3.8623809814453125e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Clique", "normalizedForm": "Clique", "offsetStart": 47, "offsetEnd": 53}, "context": "Figure 11 shows that for MNIST, when not using Clique Averaging, removing edges decreases slightly the convergence speed and increases the variance between nodes.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.03180509805679321}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 3.6954879760742188e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Clique", "normalizedForm": "Clique", "offsetStart": 54, "offsetEnd": 60}, "context": "In this first experiment, we show that D-Cliques with Clique Averaging (and momentum when mentioned) converges almost as fast as a fully-connected network on both MNIST and CIFAR10.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.19082647562026978}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.007212817668914795}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Clique", "normalizedForm": "Clique", "offsetStart": 66, "offsetEnd": 72}, "context": "In this experiment, we perform an ablation study of the effect of Clique Averaging.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.907532811164856}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9901228547096252}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Clique", "normalizedForm": "Clique", "offsetStart": 69, "offsetEnd": 75}, "context": "To ensure a fair comparison, because a random graph does not support Clique Averaging, we do not use it for D-Cliques either.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9990463852882385}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Clique", "normalizedForm": "Clique", "offsetStart": 82, "offsetEnd": 88}, "context": "This is in line with the observations made in Section 4.3 regarding the effect of Clique Averaging. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9626448750495911}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001327991485595703}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Clique", "normalizedForm": "Clique", "offsetStart": 90, "offsetEnd": 96}, "context": "Figure 5 illustrates the convergence speed of D-Cliques with n = 100 nodes on MNIST (with Clique Averaging) and CIFAR10 (with Clique Averaging and momentum).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9761645793914795}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.430511474609375e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Clique", "normalizedForm": "Clique", "offsetStart": 91, "offsetEnd": 97}, "context": "Algorithm 5 returns both W ij , for use in D-SGD (Algorithm 1 and 3), and DC, for use with Clique Averaging (Algorithm 3). ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.04181092977523804}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 4.8160552978515625e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Clique", "normalizedForm": "Clique", "offsetStart": 107, "offsetEnd": 113}, "context": "Furthermore, the use of momentum in a random graph is detrimental, similar to D-Cliques without the use of Clique Averaging (see Figure 7a).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002474188804626465}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.288818359375e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Clique", "normalizedForm": "Clique", "offsetStart": 117, "offsetEnd": 123}, "context": "(2) We design Greedy Swap, a randomized greedy algorithm for constructing such cliques efficiently; (3) We introduce Clique Averaging, a modified version of the standard D-SGD algorithm which decouples gradient averaging, used for optimizing local models, from distributed averaging, used to ensure that all models converge, thereby reducing the bias introduced by inter-clique connections;", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00043088197708129883}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.3751024603843689}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Clique", "normalizedForm": "Clique", "offsetStart": 126, "offsetEnd": 132}, "context": "Figure 5 illustrates the convergence speed of D-Cliques with n = 100 nodes on MNIST (with Clique Averaging) and CIFAR10 (with Clique Averaging and momentum).", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9761645793914795}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.430511474609375e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996814727783203}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9998295307159424}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-07}}}], "references": [], "runtime": 10678, "id": "6a1cf33eb677c46b1d5b14e62a2dae3c472e1731", "metadata": {"id": "6a1cf33eb677c46b1d5b14e62a2dae3c472e1731"}, "original_file_path": "../../datalake/Samuel/SOFTware-Sync/downloads/xml/hal-03905085.grobid.tei.xml", "file_name": "hal-03905085.grobid.tei.xml"}